abstract = {With the core objective of exploring the effects of basketball-related healthy physical training on students' cardiorespiratory health, this study utilizes systematic review and meta-analysis to delve deeper into the connection between basketball and students' cardiorespiratory fitness enhancement. A systematic review and meta-analysis were conducted to explore the effects of basketball-related physical training on students' cardiorespiratory health. Six major databases, including Scoops, Web of science, EBSCO, PubMed, China Knowledge Network (CNKI) and Wanfang, were searched for evaluation and analysis. The search was restricted to Chinese and English, and the publication period was from 2006 to 2024. Fourteen eligible studies were finally included, with a total of 881 students participating, of which the number of students in the experimental group was 442 and the number of students in the control group was 439. Continuous variables were expressed as standardized mean difference (SMD) and 95\% confidence interval (CI), and the results were pooled using random-effects meta-analysis, the quality of the literature was assessed by the Cochrane Risk of Bias tool, publication bias was examined by applying funnel plots, and meta-analysis and subgroup analyses were performed by using the Review Manager 5.4 software, and sensitivity analyses were carried out to assess the results The results of this systematic evaluation and meta-analysis showed that basketball had a significant positive effect on students' cardiorespiratory fitness, enhanced lung capacity and respiratory muscle function, and significantly improved students' cardiorespiratory fitness. It provides a scientific basis for schools and educational institutions to encourage students to participate in basketball, and promotes the overall development of students' physical and mental health.},
